"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/834270","Department for Transport","false","2018-02-08","<p>As far as can be determined, the Department centrally has 2 contracts with Capita, and the Executive Agencies in total have 15 (DVLA - 2, DVSA - 7, VCA - 2 and MCA - 4). Details of the values of these contracts are commercially sensitive.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-02-08T15:04:24.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/834270/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/834270/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/834270/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-01-31","Department for Transport: Capita","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many contracts his Department holds with Capita; and what the total value of those contracts is.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","125892"
