"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/834313","Prime Minister","false","2018-02-08","<p>Details of Trade Envoys can be found on the gov.uk website: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/groups/trade-envoys" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/groups/trade-envoys</a></p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May",,"2018-02-08T13:38:20.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/834313/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/834313/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/834313/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2018-01-31","Middle East: Trade Promotion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, whom she is appointing as trade envoys to which countries in the Middle East.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","125933"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/834314","Department for Education","false","2018-02-05","<p>The department will be issuing guidance to employers prior to the introduction of measures in April 2018 to allow levy-paying employers to transfer up to 10% of the annual value of funds entering their apprenticeship service account to another employer or an apprenticeship training agency.</p><p> </p><p>We are working closely with employers to develop an approach that supports the needs of employers of all sizes as well as the objectives of the apprenticeship programme.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2018-02-05T16:36:04.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/834314/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/834314/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/834314/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-31","Apprentices: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, when his Department plans to issue guidance on the transfer of apprenticeship vouchers between employers.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","125934"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/834315","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-02-05","<p>We recognise that the arts and culture can bring huge benefits to local communities, and this is why Arts Council England is investing over £100 million of public money into 190 theatres and touring companies over four years. Investment such as this has a positive impact on the lives of participants, it stimulates growth in the creative industries and attracts visitors.</p><p> </p><p>​Our historic £200 billion four year local authority funding settlement has also provided councils with the certainty to plan ahead and provide the services that their residents want​.​ It is for Local Authorities to decide how they invest but we are clear that investing in arts and culture is one of the best decisions local authorities can make, and, despite difficult decisions that have had to be made, many local authorities have continued to invest in arts and culture, developing innovative partnerships to support these sectors.</p>","Northampton North","Michael Ellis","126002","2018-02-05T16:20:37.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/834315/answer","Biography information for Michael Ellis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/834315/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/834315/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-01-31","Theatres","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, if his Department will assess the potential effect of the loss of the 35 theatres on the Theatres Trust at-risk register on (a) the local night-time economy (b) local employment and (c) the regeneration of local areas; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","125935"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/834316","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-02-07","<p>I refer the Hon. Member to the statement made by my Rt. Hon Friend, the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, <a href="https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2018-01-23/debates/3BEE8BA3-B281-4853-A2F7-6F787417B61D/PersonalIndependencePayment" target="_blank">Official Report</a>, 23 January 2018, Column 139.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-02-07T14:45:50.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/834316/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/834316/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/834316/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-01-31","Personal Independence Payment: Mental Health","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the timetable is for her Department to update the personal independence payment assessment guide following the judgment of RF v Secretary of State for Work And Pensions [2017] EWHC 3375 (Admin) (21 December 2017).","false","Biography information for Marsha De Cordova","Battersea","Marsha De Cordova","125936"
